{"id":9,"question":"Under Section 62, if the registered person files return within how many days of best judgement assessment order, the order shall be deemed withdrawn?","options":{"A":"7 days","B":"15 days","C":"30 days","D":"60 days"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":10,"question":"Assessment of unregistered persons liable for GST who have failed to register is done under:","options":{"A":"Section 62","B":"Section 63","C":"Section 64","D":"Section 65"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":11,"question":"Summary assessment in special cases under GST is done under:","options":{"A":"Section 62","B":"Section 63","C":"Section 64","D":"Section 65"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":12,"question":"Under Section 64 (summary assessment), prior permission is required from:","options":{"A":"Commissioner","B":"Joint/Additional Commissioner","C":"Principal Commissioner","D":"CBIC"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":13,"question":"GST audit by the tax authority is governed under:","options":{"A":"Section 61","B":"Section 63","C":"Section 65","D":"Section 73"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":14,"question":"The time limit for conducting GST audit under Section 65 is:","options":{"A":"30 days","B":"3 months (extendable by 6 months)","C":"6 months","D":"1 year"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":15,"question":"Special audit under GST is ordered under which section?","options":{"A":"Section 65","B":"Section 66","C":"Section 67","D":"Section 68"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":16,"question":"Special audit under Section 66 is conducted by:","options":{"A":"GST officer","B":"CA or CMA nominated by Commissioner","C":"Internal auditor","D":"CBIC"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":17,"question":"Power of inspection under GST is provided under:","options":{"A":"Section 65","B":"Section 66","C":"Section 67","D":"Section 68"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":18,"question":"GST demand proceedings for non-fraud cases are initiated under:","options":{"A":"Section 72","B":"Section 73","C":"Section 74","D":"Section 75"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":19,"question":"GST demand proceedings involving fraud or suppression are initiated under:","options":{"A":"Section 73","B":"Section 74","C":"Section 75","D":"Section 76"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":20,"question":"The time limit for issue of SCN under Section 73 (non-fraud) is:","options":{"A":"2 years from due date of annual return","B":"3 years from due date of annual return","C":"4 years from relevant date","D":"5 years from relevant date"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":21,"question":"The time limit for issue of SCN under Section 74 (fraud) is:","options":{"A":"3 years from relevant date","B":"4 years from relevant date","C":"5 years from relevant date","D":"6 years from relevant date"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":22,"question":"Under Section 73, if tax and interest are paid BEFORE issuance of SCN, the penalty applicable is:","options":{"A":"Nil","B":"10% of tax","C":"25% of tax","D":"50% of tax"},"answer":"A"},
{"id":23,"question":"Under Section 73, if tax, interest and 25% penalty are paid within 30 days of SCN, the proceedings shall be:","options":{"A":"Extended","B":"Deemed concluded","C":"Referred to tribunal","D":"Continued normally"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":24,"question":"Under Section 74 (fraud), if the taxpayer pays 15% penalty before SCN, the proceedings shall be:","options":{"A":"Continued","B":"Deemed concluded","C":"Referred to Commissioner","D":"Appealed"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":25,"question":"The Show Cause Notice (SCN) under GST for demand is issued in form:","options":{"A":"DRC-01","B":"DRC-02","C":"DRC-03","D":"DRC-07"},"answer":"A"},
{"id":26,"question":"The summary of order under GST (after demand proceedings) is issued in:","options":{"A":"DRC-05","B":"DRC-06","C":"DRC-07","D":"DRC-08"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":27,"question":"Voluntary payment by taxpayer under GST during proceedings is made using:","options":{"A":"DRC-01","B":"DRC-03","C":"DRC-05","D":"PMT-06"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":28,"question":"Reply to show cause notice (DRC-01) under GST is submitted in form:","options":{"A":"DRC-02","B":"DRC-04","C":"DRC-06","D":"DRC-07"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":29,"question":"Under Section 75(4), if any adverse decision is contemplated, the officer must:","options":{"A":"File appeal","B":"Give opportunity of personal hearing","C":"Issue warrant","D":"Transfer case"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":30,"question":"Interest under Section 50 of CGST Act on delayed payment of GST is charged at:","options":{"A":"12% per annum","B":"18% per annum","C":"24% per annum","D":"Depends on state"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":31,"question":"Interest under Section 50 on wrongful availment of ITC (fraudulent) is charged at:","options":{"A":"12%","B":"18%","C":"24%","D":"36%"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":32,"question":"Late fee under Section 47 of CGST Act for GSTR-3B default is:","options":{"A":"Rs.50 per day (Rs.20 for nil return)","B":"Rs.100 per day","C":"Rs.200 per day","D":"Rs.500 per day"},"answer":"A"},
{"id":33,"question":"GSTR-3B vs GSTR-1 mismatch where GSTR-1 is higher than GSTR-3B indicates:","options":{"A":"Excess ITC claimed","B":"Under-reporting of output tax liability in GSTR-3B","C":"RCM non-payment","D":"Export refund excess"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":34,"question":"GSTR-2B vs GSTR-3B mismatch where ITC in GSTR-3B is higher than GSTR-2B indicates:","options":{"A":"Short payment of output tax","B":"Excess or ineligible ITC claimed","C":"E-way bill discrepancy","D":"Wrong GSTIN used"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":35,"question":"GST demand notice for non-compliance found during audit (Section 65) is initiated under:","options":{"A":"Section 61","B":"Section 73 or 74 depending on intent","C":"Section 65 itself","D":"Section 66"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":36,"question":"GST demand confirmed in adjudication order must be paid within:","options":{"A":"15 days","B":"30 days","C":"3 months","D":"6 months"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":37,"question":"Pre-deposit required to file first GST appeal before Appellate Authority is:","options":{"A":"5% of disputed tax","B":"10% of disputed tax","C":"25% of disputed tax","D":"Full tax amount"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":38,"question":"Pre-deposit required to file appeal before GST Appellate Tribunal (GSTAT) is:","options":{"A":"10%","B":"20% of disputed amount","C":"25%","D":"30%"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":39,"question":"GST audit notice (intimation) under Section 65 is issued in form:","options":{"A":"ADT-01","B":"ADT-02","C":"ADT-03","D":"ASMT-10"},"answer":"A"},
{"id":40,"question":"GST audit report under Section 65 is issued to the taxpayer in form:","options":{"A":"ADT-01","B":"ADT-02","C":"ADT-03","D":"ADT-04"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":41,"question":"The best judgement assessment order under Section 62 is passed in form:","options":{"A":"ASMT-12","B":"ASMT-13","C":"ASMT-14","D":"ASMT-15"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":42,"question":"SCN for best judgement assessment under Section 62 is issued in form:","options":{"A":"ASMT-12","B":"ASMT-13","C":"ASMT-14","D":"ASMT-15"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":43,"question":"Under GST, which section empowers the officer to collect evidence using summons?","options":{"A":"Section 67","B":"Section 70","C":"Section 71","D":"Section 72"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":44,"question":"GST demand confirmed in assessment order carries interest from:","options":{"A":"Date of order","B":"Date of SCN","C":"Date when tax was due","D":"Date of filing return"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":45,"question":"In GST, the 'extended period of limitation' under Section 74 is triggered by:","options":{"A":"Late filing only","B":"Fraud, wilful misstatement, or suppression of facts","C":"Turnover mismatch","D":"Any non-payment"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":46,"question":"Under GST, can the officer issue SCN and pass order simultaneously?","options":{"A":"Yes, in all cases","B":"No, minimum 30 days gap between SCN and order is required","C":"Only in fraud cases","D":"Only for demand above Rs.50 lakh"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":47,"question":"Who is the first appellate authority for GST demand orders passed by officer below rank of Joint Commissioner?","options":{"A":"Commissioner (Appeals)","B":"GST Appellate Tribunal","C":"High Court","D":"Principal Commissioner"},"answer":"A"},
{"id":48,"question":"During GST scrutiny, the officer may cross-verify data with:","options":{"A":"GSTR-1 of the supplier","B":"E-way bill data","C":"Income Tax return of the taxpayer","D":"All of the above"},"answer":"D"},
{"id":49,"question":"Recovery of GST dues can be made by attachment and sale of property under:","options":{"A":"Section 78","B":"Section 79","C":"Section 80","D":"Section 81"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":50,"question":"Provisional attachment of property during GST proceedings is allowed under:","options":{"A":"Section 73","B":"Section 74","C":"Section 83","D":"Section 85"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":51,"question":"Provisional attachment under Section 83 remains valid for:","options":{"A":"6 months","B":"1 year from date of order","C":"Until final order","D":"2 years"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":52,"question":"Under GST, Section 75(12) provides recovery of confirmed tax demand as:","options":{"A":"Civil debt only","B":"Arrear of land revenue","C":"Both civil debt and arrear of land revenue","D":"Criminal fine"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":53,"question":"Which GST form is issued by the taxpayer to communicate 'no liability' in response to a notice?","options":{"A":"ASMT-11","B":"DRC-03","C":"ASMT-12","D":"REG-26"},"answer":"A"},
{"id":54,"question":"Under GST, a taxpayer can request personal hearing during adjudication under:","options":{"A":"Section 73","B":"Section 74","C":"Section 75(4)","D":"Section 76"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":55,"question":"GST proceedings can be initiated for mismatch based on information received from:","options":{"A":"Other tax departments only","B":"Only internal records","C":"Intelligence, audit findings, or any source","D":"Only taxpayer disclosure"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":56,"question":"Which GST demand scenario will attract penalty equal to 100% of tax?","options":{"A":"Clerical error in GSTR-3B","B":"Late filing of annual return","C":"Fraudulent availment of ITC with intent to defraud","D":"Wrong rate applied due to classification doubt"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":57,"question":"When a GST officer finds ITC not reversed on exempt supplies, proceedings will be under:","options":{"A":"Section 17(5)","B":"Section 73 for demand of ITC reversal with tax and interest","C":"Section 61","D":"Section 66"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":58,"question":"Under GST, 'protective demand' means:","options":{"A":"Demand to protect taxpayer","B":"Demand raised as precaution to preserve the limitation period","C":"Demand by taxpayer","D":"Demand for refund"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":59,"question":"Section 273A penalty waiver in income tax — equivalent in GST for waiver of penalty is under:","options":{"A":"Section 73(5) and 74(5) (no penalty if paid before SCN)","B":"Section 77","C":"Section 78","D":"No waiver provision"},"answer":"A"},
{"id":60,"question":"In GST, 'unjust enrichment' principle is applied primarily to:","options":{"A":"Penalty proceedings","B":"Refund claims — refund denied if tax burden passed to recipient","C":"ITC claims","D":"Assessment orders"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":61,"question":"When ITC in GSTR-3B exceeds GSTR-2B due to IGST on imports, the consultant should explain with:","options":{"A":"Reverse the ITC immediately","B":"Bill of Entry details from ICEGATE showing IGST paid, as it does not reflect in GSTR-2B","C":"Pay interest on the difference","D":"Wait for GSTR-2B to be corrected"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":62,"question":"GST notice for cancellation of registration can be issued if taxpayer:","options":{"A":"Files returns late once","B":"Continuously fails to file returns for six months (GSTR-3B) or two quarters (composition)","C":"Pays GST late","D":"Claims excess ITC once"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":63,"question":"Power of arrest under GST is provided under:","options":{"A":"Section 67","B":"Section 68","C":"Section 69","D":"Section 70"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":64,"question":"GST offences for which arrest can be made involve tax evasion exceeding:","options":{"A":"Rs.25 lakh","B":"Rs.50 lakh","C":"Rs.1 crore","D":"Rs.2 crore"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":65,"question":"No penalty shall be imposed under GST without giving:","options":{"A":"30 days' advance notice","B":"Opportunity of being heard","C":"Written warrant","D":"Department approval"},"answer":"B"},
