{"id":67,"question":"An ITC reversal due to non-payment to supplier within 180 days must be reversed in:","options":{"A":"Next GSTR-1","B":"GSTR-3B of the return period immediately following expiry of 180 days","C":"Annual return only","D":"Revised GSTR-3B"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":68,"question":"Under GST, 'credit notes' must be issued and reflected in GSTR-1 by:","options":{"A":"End of the same financial year","B":"30 November of the next financial year or date of filing annual return, whichever is earlier","C":"Any time within 2 years","D":"End of the quarter"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":69,"question":"GST Annual Return reconciliation in GSTR-9 must reconcile:","options":{"A":"Only output tax","B":"Turnover, ITC, and tax payments between GSTR-1, GSTR-3B, and books of accounts","C":"Only ITC","D":"Only payments"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":70,"question":"In GST, 'Section 16(4)' restricts ITC claims to:","options":{"A":"Current financial year only","B":"30 November of next financial year (GSTR-3B) or filing of annual return, whichever is earlier","C":"Any time if invoice is available","D":"Within 1 year of invoice date"},"answer":"B"},

# ── SECTION B: INCOME TAX SCRUTINY & FACELESS ASSESSMENT (Q71–140) ─────────
{"id":71,"question":"Notice for Income Tax scrutiny assessment is issued under:","options":{"A":"Section 142(1)","B":"Section 143(1)","C":"Section 143(2)","D":"Section 147"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":72,"question":"Time limit for issuing scrutiny notice under Section 143(2) is:","options":{"A":"3 months from filing","B":"6 months from end of FY of filing","C":"12 months from end of AY","D":"Anytime within 4 years"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":73,"question":"Scrutiny assessment order under Section 143(3) is called:","options":{"A":"Summary assessment","B":"Best judgment assessment","C":"Scrutiny assessment","D":"Precautionary assessment"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":74,"question":"The primary notice calling for books/documents during income tax scrutiny is under:","options":{"A":"Section 143(2)","B":"Section 142(1)","C":"Section 131","D":"Section 133"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":75,"question":"Section 142(1) empowers the Assessing Officer to:","options":{"A":"Pass assessment order","B":"Call for return, accounts, or specific information before or after return filing","C":"Conduct search","D":"Attach property"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":76,"question":"Income Tax faceless assessment is conducted under:","options":{"A":"Section 143(3) only","B":"Section 143(3) read with Section 144B","C":"Section 147","D":"Section 144"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":77,"question":"The central body overseeing faceless assessment in Income Tax is:","options":{"A":"CBDT","B":"CPC Bengaluru","C":"National Faceless Assessment Centre (NFAC)","D":"Regional Assessment Centre"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":78,"question":"In faceless assessment, the Assessment Unit (AU) is responsible for:","options":{"A":"Technical analysis","B":"Making the assessment (examining returns and issuing show cause/draft order)","C":"Verifying fieldwork","D":"Handling appeals"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":79,"question":"In faceless assessment, the Verification Unit (VU) is responsible for:","options":{"A":"Making the assessment","B":"Verifying documents, making field inquiries, and issuing notices for verification","C":"Technical analysis on valuation/TP","D":"Review of draft order"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":80,"question":"In faceless assessment, the Technical Unit (TU) provides:","options":{"A":"Makes the assessment","B":"Technical assistance on legal, accounting, forensic, IT, valuation, and transfer pricing matters","C":"Verification in field","D":"Review of AU orders"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":81,"question":"The Review Unit (RU) in faceless assessment is responsible for:","options":{"A":"Conducting appeals","B":"Reviewing draft assessment orders for errors before finalization","C":"Verifying TDS returns","D":"Auditing taxpayers"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":82,"question":"Under Section 144B, personal hearing in faceless assessment is conducted through:","options":{"A":"Physical appearance before officer","B":"Video Conference (VC) facility on request","C":"Written submissions only; no hearing allowed","D":"Only for demand above Rs.10 lakh"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":83,"question":"In faceless assessment, the identity of the officer handling the case is:","options":{"A":"Disclosed to taxpayer","B":"Not disclosed — the assessment is anonymous","C":"Disclosed only to authorized representative","D":"Disclosed on completion"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":84,"question":"Selection of Income Tax returns for scrutiny is primarily done through:","options":{"A":"Manual selection by AO only","B":"CASS (Computer Aided Scrutiny Selection) system","C":"Taxpayer's request","D":"CBDT specific mandate"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":85,"question":"Assessment under Section 144 (best judgement assessment) is made when:","options":{"A":"Return is filed correctly","B":"Taxpayer fails to comply with notices or does not file return despite notice","C":"Only for foreign income","D":"Company assessments only"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":86,"question":"'Limited scrutiny' in Income Tax focuses on:","options":{"A":"All aspects of return","B":"Specific issues identified at the time of selection","C":"Only capital gains","D":"Only business income"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":87,"question":"'Complete scrutiny' in Income Tax means:","options":{"A":"Specific issue examination","B":"Examination of all aspects of the return","C":"Only deduction verification","D":"Audit under 44AB only"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":88,"question":"Rectification of mistakes in an Income Tax assessment order is done under:","options":{"A":"Section 147","B":"Section 154","C":"Section 148","D":"Section 263"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":89,"question":"Section 154 allows rectification of mistakes that are:","options":{"A":"Matters of opinion or law","B":"Apparent on the face of the record","C":"Disputed by taxpayer","D":"Covered by appeal only"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":90,"question":"Time limit for rectification under Section 154 is:","options":{"A":"1 year","B":"2 years","C":"4 years from end of FY when order was passed","D":"6 years"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":91,"question":"Under Section 144B, if any variation is proposed in faceless assessment, draft order must be provided to taxpayer if:","options":{"A":"Always for all cases","B":"When any addition or disallowance is proposed (any variation)","C":"Only for demand above Rs.10 lakh","D":"Only for companies"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":92,"question":"Taxpayer's response to draft order in faceless assessment must be filed within:","options":{"A":"7 days","B":"15 days","C":"30 days","D":"45 days"},"answer":"C"},
