{"id":94,"question":"Penalty for non-compliance with notice under Section 272A (e.g., failure to comply with 142(1)) is:","options":{"A":"Rs.5,000","B":"Rs.10,000","C":"0.5% of turnover","D":"Rs.25,000"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":95,"question":"Section 133 empowers the Income Tax officer to call for information from:","options":{"A":"Only the taxpayer","B":"Any person including banks, companies, local bodies","C":"Only registrars","D":"Only government departments"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":96,"question":"Section 131 empowers the Income Tax officer with powers of:","options":{"A":"Search and seizure","B":"Civil court for discovery, inspection, and compelling attendance","C":"Criminal court","D":"Revenue recovery"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":97,"question":"Income Tax survey under Section 133A is restricted to:","options":{"A":"Residence of the taxpayer","B":"Business premises during business hours","C":"Any premises anytime","D":"Only registered premises"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":98,"question":"Income Tax search and seizure is authorized under:","options":{"A":"Section 132","B":"Section 133","C":"Section 133A","D":"Section 134"},"answer":"A"},
{"id":99,"question":"Authorization for Income Tax search must be issued by an officer not below the rank of:","options":{"A":"Inspector","B":"Assessing Officer","C":"Joint Director or Joint Commissioner","D":"Commissioner"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":100,"question":"Assessment following search and seizure is done under:","options":{"A":"Section 143(3)","B":"Section 144","C":"Section 153A","D":"Section 153B"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":101,"question":"Assessment under Section 153A covers:","options":{"A":"Only current AY","B":"6 AYs preceding year of search (plus block period AY)","C":"10 years","D":"Only 2 years"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":102,"question":"Under Income Tax scrutiny, additions can be made on account of:","options":{"A":"Unexplained investments only","B":"Unexplained income, disallowed expenditure, and any income not offered to tax","C":"Only disallowed expenditure","D":"Only undisclosed income"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":103,"question":"'Addition' in Income Tax scrutiny context means:","options":{"A":"Filing a revised return","B":"Income added to declared income by the AO after examining the return","C":"Claiming additional deduction","D":"Depositing additional tax"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":104,"question":"Against scrutiny assessment order, the first appeal lies to:","options":{"A":"ITAT","B":"High Court","C":"Commissioner of Income Tax (Appeals) — CIT(A)","D":"Principal Commissioner"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":105,"question":"Form 35 is used for:","options":{"A":"Filing original return","B":"Filing first appeal before CIT(A)","C":"Filing appeal before ITAT","D":"Revision application"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":106,"question":"In Income Tax, 'draft assessment order' under faceless scheme must be provided when:","options":{"A":"Always","B":"Any variation is proposed — additions, disallowances, or any adverse inference","C":"Only for demand above Rs.10 lakh","D":"Only for companies"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":107,"question":"Under Section 153D, completion of search assessment requires prior approval of:","options":{"A":"CBDT","B":"Joint/Additional Commissioner","C":"Commissioner","D":"Principal CIT"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":108,"question":"In faceless assessment, the Income Tax officer issues orders through:","options":{"A":"Physical dispatch only","B":"ITBA portal / electronic mode (e-proceedings)","C":"Registered post only","D":"Email to taxpayer directly"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":109,"question":"Under Section 144C, the DRP (Dispute Resolution Panel) consists of:","options":{"A":"1 Principal Commissioner","B":"2 Principal Commissioners","C":"3 Principal Commissioners or Commissioners","D":"5 Commissioners"},"answer":"C"},
