{"id":111,"question":"Before initiating reassessment under Section 147, the AO must issue notice under:","options":{"A":"Section 131","B":"Section 142(1)","C":"Section 148","D":"Section 133"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":112,"question":"Section 148A procedure (prior opportunity) requires the AO to:","options":{"A":"Directly issue Section 148 notice","B":"Provide opportunity to the assessee before issuing Section 148 notice, including sharing information","C":"Seek court permission","D":"Get CBDT approval"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":113,"question":"Under Section 149, time limit for issuing Section 148 notice for income escaped above Rs.50 lakh is:","options":{"A":"3 years","B":"5 years","C":"10 years from end of relevant AY","D":"7 years"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":114,"question":"The normal time limit for Section 148 notice (income escaped below Rs.50 lakh) is:","options":{"A":"1 year","B":"2 years","C":"3 years from end of relevant AY","D":"5 years"},"answer":"C"},
{"id":115,"question":"Revision of assessment order by Commissioner under Section 263 requires the order to be:","options":{"A":"Correct but incomplete","B":"Erroneous and prejudicial to the interests of revenue","C":"Against taxpayer","D":"Any order older than 1 year"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":116,"question":"Time limit for revision under Section 263 by CIT is:","options":{"A":"1 year","B":"2 years from end of FY when order was passed","C":"3 years","D":"No limit"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":117,"question":"Revision under Section 264 (by CIT) is in favor of:","options":{"A":"Revenue","B":"Assessee","C":"Both equally","D":"Only for arithmetical mistakes"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":118,"question":"In scrutiny proceedings, the 'burden of proof' primarily lies with:","options":{"A":"The department","B":"The assessee to explain sources of income and investments","C":"ITAT","D":"Shared equally always"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":119,"question":"In Income Tax scrutiny, 'telescoping' refers to:","options":{"A":"Relating one disclosed source to explain an unexplained item of income/expense","B":"Filing multiple returns","C":"Adjusting deductions","D":"Carrying forward losses"},"answer":"A"},
{"id":120,"question":"'Third party information' used against the taxpayer in scrutiny:","options":{"A":"Need not be disclosed","B":"Must be disclosed to taxpayer as it is the basis of addition — principles of natural justice","C":"Disclosed only if demanded","D":"Disclosed only on court order"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":121,"question":"National Faceless Appeal Centre (NFAC) handles appeals under:","options":{"A":"Section 143(3)","B":"Section 246A — first appeals before CIT(A)","C":"Section 263","D":"Section 154"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":122,"question":"The principle of 'natural justice' in Income Tax proceedings requires:","options":{"A":"Only notice to be issued","B":"Proper notice, opportunity to be heard, and reasoned order","C":"Only order to be passed","D":"Only opportunity to pay"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":123,"question":"If Income Tax AO relies on a report or information not disclosed to assessee:","options":{"A":"The addition is valid","B":"The addition may be invalid on grounds of violation of natural justice","C":"The assessment is automatic","D":"No objection can be raised"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":124,"question":"In faceless assessment, the RFAC (Regional Faceless Assessment Centre) receives cases from:","options":{"A":"Taxpayer directly","B":"NFAC which allocates cases to RFAC and assigns to Assessment Units","C":"CPC only","D":"State tax department"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":125,"question":"'Protective assessment' in Income Tax refers to:","options":{"A":"Assessment to protect taxpayer interests","B":"Assessment as a precautionary measure while the substantive/primary assessment is pending elsewhere","C":"Assessment under guarantee","D":"Best judgement assessment"},"answer":"B"},
{"id":126,"question":"Under Income Tax, 'Panchnama' refers to:","options":{"A":"Five-year tax plan","B":"Document recording proceedings during search and seizure prepared by witnesses","C":"Form for survey","D":"Annual assessment report"},"answer":"B"},
